  "texts": [
    "Unless otherwise specified, a random 8:1:1 train:validation:test split is applied to USPTO-ORD-100K to train/evaluate models throughout this study.",
    "This data pipeline is schematically shown in Figure 1.",
    "The information in a structured ORD record is not guaranteed to be a proper subset of its free text description, as some information in the structured ORD record is derived from elsewhere, and in this work denoted \"implicit information\".",
    "For example, the reaction roles of compounds are rarely stated in a reaction's text description.",
    "As another example, the text description may indicate a filtration step (mapping to a ReactionWorkup of type FILTRATION in its ORD record) but does not include \"filter\" or \"filtration\" explicitly, e.g., \"passing through celite\"."
